text: Joined the Arizona Border Counties Coalition meeting today to discuss the ongoing border crisis. As this crisis worsens, #AZ06 border communities pay the price. This isn’t political, we must prioritize and secure our border.

Speaker McCarthy’s removal is pointless, unproductive and harmful to the agenda we put forth when we were elected. 

More from me. ⬇️

.@HouseGOP have passed bills to restore American energy independence, claw back wasteful spending & secure the border with the strongest border security bill in years.

We have 45 days to fund our priorities. There's no time to waste. I stand with @SpeakerMcCarthy to get it done.

Today I supported a temporary funding package to keep our government open. Plain & simple: this was not my first, second, or even third choice. In my first nine months in Congress, I have seen just how broken Washington is and nothing sums it up quite like the last few weeks. While this bill wasn’t what I would have liked to see, it was the only option on the table to avoid a shutdown at this point. A shutdown would have had a catastrophic impact on our border, military, and government services. 

The work is far from done. The house MUST swiftly pass full-year, fiscally responsible appropriations bills that rein in the out of control spending by the Biden administration.

Yesterday I voted to SECURE our border & keep our government OPEN.

While this effort didn’t pass, I’m committed to finding a solution to ensure our government doesn’t shutdown. We have less than 24 hours to do so & are staying in D.C. through the weekend. Nobody wins with a shutdown, nobody.

Special edition of the #CiscomaniMinute to give you a rundown of what happened this week as Congress works to keep our government open.

I’ve made my position clear — I am committed to avoiding a shutdown. More below in this week’s video. ⬇️

Thrilled to see the House PASS a well-deserved pay raise for our troops in this year’s defense appropriations package.
 
The Senate needs move quickly to get this bill across the finish line and to the president’s desk. Our military deserves nothing less than our utmost support.

We need to come to the table and negotiate a path forward. Over the next two days, my priority remains the same: keeping our government open and maintaining services for veterans, seniors, and taxpayers.

After last night’s votes, the House has now passed 4 funding bills, significant progress from earlier this week. However, we’re still running down the clock. We have less than 48 hours to avoid a government shutdown and the Senate has yet to pass a single funding bill.

Walking off the floor just a few minutes shy of midnight here in D.C. 

My thoughts on tonight’s votes ⬇️

Nobody wins in a government shutdown.
